@byronyi - can you please explain the objection a bit more?
Both CUDA Runtime (cudaMalloc) and CUDA Driver (cuMemAlloc) APIs are proprietary, right?
NVIDIA folks suggest applications to use the CUDA Runtime API and not the Driver API. Is there any particular need to use the CUDA Driver API in TensorFlow?

